      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Gaythorne property values are driven by the suburb's position in Brisbane's northern corridor, its character Queenslander homes on generous residential blocks, proximity to Mitchelton Station on the Ferny Grove line, and the school catchments that attract committed family buyers. The suburb offers a genuine leafy-northern-Brisbane lifestyle at a price point that has historically sat below the more tightly held addresses of neighbouring Alderley and Mitchelton, which draws families who have been comparing the corridor and want the lifestyle without paying the full Alderley premium. Low stock turnover supports consistent buyer competition when properties do come to market." }
    },
