      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does it take to sell a home in Gaythorne?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Well-priced Gaythorne homes typically sell within 25 to 40 days. The suburb attracts motivated family buyers who have been researching the northern corridor and have identified Gaythorne as a compelling value option adjacent to Alderley and Mitchelton. Because these buyers have already done their homework on the corridor, they tend to act decisively when a well-presented property appears at a price that reflects the genuine market. Autumn and spring bring the strongest campaign conditions, but the suburb draws consistent interest throughout the year from buyers who cannot find what they want in the tighter neighbouring addresses." }
    },
